  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "Season the tempeh with cayenne pepper, paprika, cinnamon, salt, and black pepper.",
    "In a pan, heat the ghee over medium heat; add sliced ginger and cook for 2 minutes.",
    "Add the ras el hanout, honey, coriander, and water to the pan; stirring to combine.",
    "Add the tempeh to the pan, coating it evenly with the spice mixture.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 20cm (8in) round baking dish or cast-iron skillet.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, then remove from the oven and spread the raspberry jam evenly on top of the tempeh mixture.",
    "Return the dish to the oven and continue baking for an additional 15 minutes, or until the cheese is gooey and the jam has caramelized.",
    "Remove from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving."
  ],
